															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=617958&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250568" alt="Communism will win" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=617958)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;" >Communism will win</a></span> <span class="odate time_1361676340 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Feb 2013 03:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1717884">
									

<p>This is my first foray into another team's canon. As you might notice, all of these SCPs are mine. I apologize for nothing.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Edit:&nbsp;Some&nbsp;backstory&nbsp;that&nbsp;I&nbsp;like&nbsp;but&nbsp;haven't&nbsp;ever&nbsp;spelled&nbsp;out</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Regarding&nbsp;some&nbsp;recurring&nbsp;characters&nbsp;and&nbsp;places</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>In the last vignette, in which Subject <a href="/scp-1564">1564-18</a> mentions that she was once called Jyoti Sanmugasunderam, it's not a coincidence that I reused the name from <a href="/misnomer">Misnomer</a> &#8212; Jyoti is Satyana's younger sister who got recruited to D-class (the elder Sanmugasunderam was not informed of this, as the identities of all D-class are kept secret). It's up to you whether Coldest War and Competitive Dicksatology are co-canons or whether the same characters simply exist in multiple universes. <a href="/scp-1564">SCP-1564</a>'s article, by the way, is set a ways in time after <a href="/misnomer">Misnomer</a> (hence the elder Sanmugasunderam's receiving of a Doctorate), but about ten years before this tale. I have an explanation for <em>why</em> these people are interacting this way, but it's not particularly relevant to anything else that's happening. At least at the moment.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

